metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #193
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Washed Trees Fluor #44
metadata.description:
‚ÄúOur Love had heard that an immortal language never could die, although silent, it still slept somewhere amongst the birches, lost ever since the day when we went weeping from beneath the angel-guarded gates of Eden.‚Äù

In Inner Purple Forest ‚ÄúWashed Trees Fluor‚Äù, rainbow bubbles-shaped form sprouts like fungi from a birch log. 

With its disconcerting conjunction of the natural and man-made, this still life recalls the way that nutrients in dead plant material are reclaimed by other living things as part of nature‚Äôs cycle of decay and rebirth.

No matter how long or hard we might gaze upon these ghostly images remain the same, they are not allowed to gather too much dust, they do not lose their bloom.

metadata.name: Broken Tiles #62
metadata.description:
This is an homage to all the cheap tacky tiles around the world.

Broken Tiles is initiated by first generating a grid. The grid is then superimposed with Voronoi pattern and displaced with the same grid, resulting in broken and cracked effect. All texture and pattern are generated with nodes in cables.gl, no PNG texture image is used.

Press [s] to capture a 1920x1920 screenshot.



XALTED 2022
